      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Even a small amount of St. John's wort can still interfere with sertraline by lowering your seizure threshold or increasing serotonin levels, which can be dangerous. Your symptoms likely stem from the combination of stress and how your brain processes both the medication and low mood, so adding another influence without medical guidance is risky. It is much safer to talk to your doctor about adjusting your dose or adding a supportive therapy temporarily instead of experimenting with over-the-counter supplements.",
      "source": "target",
